class QgsDropFeedbackOverlay : QWidget
{
%Docstring(signature="appended")
A translucent overlay widget which renders visual feedback while a drag
carrying map layers, a project or an unloadable payload hovers a widget
which accepts such drops (e.g. the layer tree view or the map canvas).

The overlay is transparent for mouse events and does not accept drops
itself, so it never interferes with the drag and drop event delivery of
the widget it covers. It is meant to be laid over a target widget
(matching its geometry), shown while a drag hovers and hidden on drop or
drag leave.

Nothing is drawn for :py:class:`Qgis`.LayerDropPayloadType.Layers or
:py:class:`Qgis`.LayerDropPayloadType.CustomHandler payloads, for which
the hosting widget provides its own (or no) feedback.

.. versionadded:: 4.4
%End

%TypeHeaderCode
#include "qgsdropfeedbackoverlay.h"
%End
  public:
    explicit QgsDropFeedbackOverlay( QWidget *parent /TransferThis/ = 0 );
%Docstring
Constructor for QgsDropFeedbackOverlay, with the specified ``parent``
widget.
%End

    void setPayloadType( Qgis::LayerDropPayloadType type );
%Docstring
Sets the ``type`` of payload to render feedback for, triggering a
repaint.

.. seealso:: :py:func:`payloadType`
%End

    Qgis::LayerDropPayloadType payloadType() const;
%Docstring
Returns the type of payload the overlay currently renders feedback for.

.. seealso:: :py:func:`setPayloadType`
%End

    static void paintFeedback( QPainter *painter, const QRect &rect, Qgis::LayerDropPayloadType payloadType, const QWidget *widget );
%Docstring
Renders the drop feedback for ``payloadType`` into ``rect`` using
``painter``.

Nothing is drawn for :py:class:`Qgis`.LayerDropPayloadType.Layers or
:py:class:`Qgis`.LayerDropPayloadType.CustomHandler payloads.

The ``widget`` supplies the palette, font and device pixel ratio used
for themed, hidpi-aware rendering. This is exposed so that widgets which
prefer to paint the feedback directly (e.g. within their own
:py:func:`~QgsDropFeedbackOverlay.paintEvent`) can reuse the exact same
rendering without hosting an overlay widget.
%End

  protected:
    virtual void paintEvent( QPaintEvent *event );


};

